title: Orleans coroner identifies two homicide victims
content:
NEW ORLEANS (WVUE) -
The Orleans Parish Coroner has identified two men shot to death in separate incidents on Thursday.
Leonard Moses, 26, was shot and killed in the 6100 block of Tullis Drive in Algiers. Another man and a six-month-old baby were also injured in that shooting.
The infant remains in serious condition after surgery.
Robert Atkins 21, was found shot to death in on Florida Avenue in the Lower Ninth Ward Thursday afternoon.
